{{Infobox journal | title = Third Text | cover = Third Text Magazine.jpg | discipline = [[Visual arts]] | editor = [[Rasheed Araeen]] | publisher = [[Routledge]] | country = | history = 1987-present | frequency = Bimonthly | website = http://www.thirdtext.org/ | language = English, French | ISSN = 0952-8822 | abbreviation = Third Text }} '''''Third Text''''' is a bimonthly [[academic journal]] on [[world art studies|art in global context]].<ref name="urlTaylor & Francis Journals: Welcome">{{cite web |url=http://www.tandf.co.uk/journals/titles/09528822.html |title=Taylor & Francis Journals: Journal Details: Third Text|work= |accessdate=2008-08-24}}</ref> After founder and editor [[Rasheed Araeen]]'s earlier [[art magazine]] ''Black Phoenix'', started in 1978, published only three issues, it was relaunched as a theoretical art journal in 1987.<ref name="art of resistance">{{cite web |url=http://www.dawn.com/2003/02/09/local6.htm |title=KARACHI: Artist stresses art of resistance | date=February 9, 2003 |work=[[Dawn (newspaper)|Dawn]] |accessdate=2008-08-24}}</ref> From 1992 - 1999 the journal was edited by [[Jean Fisher]]. ''Third Text'' challenges the boundaries of the [[visual arts]] and the confines of the Western academy, featuring leading critics alongside new voices and advanced scholarship interspersed with radical interdisciplinary work that goes beyond the confines of [[Eurocentricity]].
